solutions.content:
# Intuition
Since we will have to use previous calculation to reach the end result we will be using Dyanmic programing to solve this. The thogugh for DP is to always think about what would happen for ith day.

dp[i] will represent the min cost till that day.

So on ith day one of the following would occur
- We buy a one day ticket i.e one day before cost + 1 day ticket cost which looks like dp[i-1] + costs[0].
- We buy a seven day valid ticket which is dp[i-7] + costs[1]. ****But catch here is that we may still be at day 5(index 5) so 5-7 = -2 so that is a case we need to handle so dp[Math.max(0,i-7)] + costs[1]****
- We 30 days pass dp[Math.max(0,i-30)] + costs[2]

*The underflow condition where we do Math.max(0, i-x) is imp and comes to mind only with practice*


---


# Approach
1) Define dp array to n+1 length where n is the max day we need to travel i.e days[length-1] element.
2) Since we don't visit all the days we will maintain a boolean travel day array or Set anything would work
3) We traverse through all days and calculate
4) If the day is not in travel list cost remains same as what it costed us for last day i.e dp[i] = dp[i-1] where ith day is not travelled one
5) For travelled day i have explained above.
6) Return the value at last index of dp

To understand different type of DP see this [Leetcode award wining article](https://leetcode.com/discuss/general-discussion/458695/dynamic-programming-patterns) that helped me during my prepartion time
---


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n) Since we are travesing the days array once.

- Space complexity:
O(n) for the DP array

---


# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int mincostTickets(int[] days, int[] costs) {

        int maxDay = days[days.length-1];
        boolean [] travelDay = new boolean[maxDay+1];
        for(int day: days){
            travelDay[day] =true;
        }
        int [] dp = new int[maxDay+1];
        dp[0]=0;

        for(int i=1;i<=maxDay;i++){
            if(!travelDay[i]){
                //dont have to buy a ticket if it is not a travel day
                dp[i]=dp[i-1]; 
                continue;
            }
            dp[i] = costs[0]+dp[i-1];
            dp[i] = Math.min(dp[Math.max(0,i-7)]+costs[1],dp[i]);
            dp[i] = Math.min(dp[Math.max(0,i-30)]+costs[2],dp[i]);
        }
        return dp[maxDay];
    }
}
```
