solutions.content:
# Intuition

On each day, we need to look into future days and analyze if purchasing a 7 day or a 30 day pass will be benefitial.
- Weird scenario is when 30 day pass will be cheapest, the we can purchase that even for one day. But we ignore such cases in explaination since our answer also covers these cases
- So in other scenarios, getting a 7 day is benefitial if we need to travel multiple time in next seven days and cost of one 7 day pass would be less than purchasing one day pass multiple times for those days.
- If 7 day pass is cheaper and better then we can purchase that, but it might be possible that we are travelling a lot in not just 7 days but in next 30 days and getting a 30 day pass might be even cheaper
- So for each day, we look forward and find how many times we travel in next 7 days/ 30 days and calculate cost related to each option and choose the minimum.
- This is recursive problem since cost is Minimum of three available options
  - Get a one day pass and add rest of cost from next day onwards
  - Get a 7 day pass and add this cost and cost for remaining days after this 7 day pass expires 
  - Get a 30 day pass and add this cost and cost for remaining days after this 30 day pass expires 

# Approach
If we follow recursive approach we will get TLE, since multilple earlier days will require answer for later day and will make multiple calls but we can store the result i.e use DP to optimize.

 So we maintain a DP array and start from last day and calculate cost for last day, then second last day and then so on.

On any particular day, we check how many days we travel in next 7/ 30 days and then add the cost of pass + the cost from the day in future when pass would have expired

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$ Since we calculate values for DP array n times: for each time we can look forward upto a max 30 elements. So Actual complexity is 30*O(n) but for large n, 30 is a constant hence final complexity is O(n) only. 

- Space complexity:
$$O(n)$$ Since we maintain a DP array of size n.

