# INTUTION 

##### •	The problem is to find the minimum cost to buy passes to travel on a given set of days. We can solve this problem using dynamic programming.
##### •	We can define a recursive function minCost(days, costs, pass, index, dp) that returns the minimum cost to travel for the remaining days starting from the given index. We can use memoization to avoid recomputing the same subproblems.
##### •	At each step, we can try all three types of passes (1-day, 7-day, and 30-day passes) and choose the one that gives the minimum cost. To find the cost of a pass, we need to add the cost of the pass to the cost of traveling for the remaining days after the pass expires.
##### •	To find the index of the next day after a pass expires, we can use a loop to find the first day that is after the current day plus the duration of the pass.
##### •	The base case of the recursion is when we have covered all the days. In this case, the cost is 0.

