# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Okay, we are first of all we are creating the dp array to store our previous calculation, and initializating ```dp[n]``` with 0 we will talk about that latter.

Also we have to supporting methods ```skipWeek``` and ```skipMonth``` this methods trying to find day after our 7-day pass and 30-day pass. 
In ```skipWeek``` we returning first day that are larger than ```days[index] + 6``` (this day and six next days) or ```days.size()```, that mean in ```days``` there are no "travel" days after end of 7-day pass from ```days[index]```  to ```days[index] + 6```.
```skipMonth``` works same as ```skipWeek``` but now we are trying to find next "travel" day after end of 30-day pass.


After initializating all, we run loop from ```n-1``` to ```0``` at each iteration we are trying to get how much money we spent earlier. 
```costIfTakeDay``` - amount of money spent earlier plus ```cost[0]``` . That means how much we spent earlier and if for this day we will take 1-day ticket.
```costIfTakeWeek``` - amount of money spent earlier plus ```cost[1]```. That means how much we spent earlier and if for this day we will take 7-day ticket. If there are no days before function ```skipWeek``` will return ```days.size()```, but we already initialized ```dp[days.size()] = 0;``` and the cost of travel from ```days[index]``` will cost like a 7-day pass
```costIfTakeMonth``` - - amount of money spent earlier plus ```cost[2]```. Means same as ```costIfTakeWeek``` but calls  ```skipMonth``` function.


# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n^2)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int mincostTickets(vector<int> &days, vector<int> &costs) {
        int n = days.size();
        auto dp = std::vector<::uint16_t>(n+1, 1001);
        dp[n] = 0;

        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
            int costIfTakeDay = dp[i + 1] + costs[0];
            int costIfTakeWeek = dp[skipWeek(i, days)] + costs[1];
            int costIfTakeMonth = dp[skipMonth(i, days)] + costs[2];

            dp[i] = std::min({costIfTakeDay, costIfTakeMonth, costIfTakeWeek});
        }
        return dp[0];
    }

    int skipWeek(int index, std::vector<int> &days) {
        int lastDayOfWeekTicket = days[index] + 6;
        for (auto i = index; i < days.size(); ++i) {
            if (days[i] > lastDayOfWeekTicket)
                return i;
        }
        return days.size();
    }

    int skipMonth(int index, std::vector<int> &days) {
        int lastDayOfMonthTicket = days[index] + 29;
        for (auto i = index; i < days.size(); ++i) {
            if (days[i] > lastDayOfMonthTicket)
                return i;
        }
        return days.size();
    }
};
```

