Bottom up is so hard to come up with. Hence, be advised to start with recursion and get TLE and change it to memoization. Pretty simple, no?

Time : O(n)
Space : O(n)

Please let me know if you have any doubts. And do not forget to **upvote**.

```java
public int mincostTickets(int[] days, int[] costs) {

	int n = days.length;

	Integer[] memo = new Integer[n];

	return minCostTicketsHelper(days, 0, costs, memo);
}

private int minCostTicketsHelper(int[] days, int index, int[] costs, Integer[] memo) {

	if (index >= days.length) return 0;

	if (memo[index] != null) return memo[index];

	int x = costs[0] + minCostTicketsHelper(days, index + 1, costs, memo);

	int next = index;
	for (; next < days.length && days[next] < days[index] + 7; next++);

	int y = costs[1] + minCostTicketsHelper(days, next, costs, memo);

	next = index;
	for (; next < days.length && days[next] < days[index] + 30; next++);

	int z = costs[2] + minCostTicketsHelper(days, next, costs, memo);

	memo[index] = Math.min(x, Math.min(y, z));
	return memo[index];
}

