# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
First we will attempt with recursion then we will optimse time complexcity because of covering subproblems by 1 d dp
Instinct is that we will purchase tickets/vouchers just when we experience a substantial travelling day
Then at the end we'll return the minimum of all the possibilities

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Now you know the sub problems so we can convert OUR recursion solution to top-down-memoization , ie we store our answers at each step before returning, then if we already knows the answer , we can return right back without re calculating

- For each day index of days array, three possibilities are considered:
For each day that you need to buy a ticket you will try the three options

i) Buying a one-day ticket and then continuing with the rest of the days
ii) Buying a seven-day ticket and skipping all the days included in this ticket
iii) Buying a thirty-day ticket and skipping all the days included in this ticket
 as in top down DP approach, we store the results into the array(here in 1D array as needed) so that we can directly return the answer already stored if we traver again onto that index.
so before returning the answer at any index, we store it into the MEMO( DP ) array, for future use.
this helps us reduce the time complexity(of recursive solution) from  3^n to much good(acchi acchi time complexity) time complexity;


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
As we travel only once throught the days array, 
TC comes out to be : O(N) 

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
we use extra space (in memoised solution) of size N,
therefore O(N) space complexity

