# ****To Solve this problem we will take a dynamic array of size 366 and start travese it from one as dp[0] = 0 No cost for 0th day, Now for each day we will check the cost for 3 tickets and take minimum of it ----> Math.min(dp[i] =  dp[i-1] + costs[0] , dp[i] = dp[i-7] + costs[1], dp[i]  = dp[i-30] + costs[2]) this we will do when the ith day is in our days array otherwise we will simply store dp[i]= dp[i-1] and for optimisation we will break when our j pointer reaches days.length**


```
class Solution {
    public int mincostTickets(int[] days, int[] costs) {
        int dp[] = new int[366];
        dp[0]=0;
        int j=0;
        for(int i=1;i<366;i++){
            if(j==days.length){
                break;
            }

            if(days[j] != i){
                dp[i] = dp[i-1];
            }
            else{
                int one = dp[i-1] + costs[0];
                int seven = dp[Math.max(0,i-7)] + costs[1];
                int thirty = dp[Math.max(0,i-30)] + costs[2];
                dp[i] = Math.min(one, Math.min(seven, thirty));
                j++;
            }
        }
        return dp[days[days.length-1]];
    }
}
