# Intuition & Approach
- Explained in the code

# Complexity
- Time complexity:$O(lastDay+1)$

- Space complexity:$O(lastDay+1)$

# Code
```
class Solution
{
    public:
       LOGIC

    KARNA KYA HAIN❓
    1. We are given some integers in the list days.
    2. We can travel if we have a valid train ticket for that day.
    3. There are three ticket options.
    -  valid for 1 day at costs[0] dollars.
    -  valid for 7 day at costs[1] dollars.
    -  valid for 30 day at costs[2] dollars.
    4. We need to return the min cost that is required to travel on every day that
       is  given.

    INTUITION & APPROACH
    1. 2 important things to notice in this problem
    - As we iterate we have to decide ki whether for that day we have a valid pass
    or we have to buy one.
    - Also we need to decide which ticket to buy which affects future decisions.

    2. So this is a problem of DP and Recursion
    Why❓
    - Each decision we make is affected by previous decision we made.
    - The problem is asking to find the minimum cost required.

    3. Agar hamare paas ticket hain jis din ham travel kar rahe to koi dikkat nahin
    aage wale din check karenge is din koi extra cost nahin.
    4. Agar ticket nahin hain to hamare paas 3 choices hongi 1,7 and 30 day passed.
    5. Baari Baari se recursive call karenge aur teeno ka min nikalnege.
    💥Recurrence relation mentioned in memoization code.
    6. The parameter which is changing is the currDay.
    7. BASE CASE :- currDay>days[days.length-1] return 0.
    8. We will create a hash set which will contain days on which we travel.
    9. In recursiveFunction we will check the currDay in this hash set and decide
    if we have the valid ticket or not.
    10. RECURSION -> MEMOIZATION -> TABULATION 
    11. MEMOIZATION STEPS
    - Which parameter is changing
    - Declare dp array
    - Store the dp values
    - Check if the dp value is already stored.
    12. TABULATION
    - In this we will not keep a hash set but a variable i.
    - i will keep track of the days we have to visit.
    - While iterating the days from 1 to the largest day possible we will check it
    with index i if the day is smaller than days[i] if yes then this day is valid,
    cost is same as that of prev day and no extra cost is incurred otherwise 
    we will check all three day passed and find min.

//=========================================================================================================

       	//MEMOIZATION SOLUTION
        unordered_set<int> isTicketValid;
    int Memoization(vector<int> &dp, vector<int> &days, vector< int > &costs, int currDay)
    {
        if (currDay > days[days.size() - 1])
        //BASE CASE
        //If the current day exceeds last Day
            return 0;
        if (dp[currDay] != -1)
        //If we have already calculated the val for currDay
            return dp[currDay];
        if (isTicketValid.find(currDay) == isTicketValid.end())
        //Checking if the currDay is a day on which we had to travel
            return Memoization(dp, days, costs, currDay + 1);
        int oneDay = costs[0] + Memoization(dp, days, costs, currDay + 1);
        //One day path
        int sevenDay = costs[1] + Memoization(dp, days, costs, currDay + 7);
        //seven day path
        int thirtyDay = costs[2] + Memoization(dp, days, costs, currDay + 30);
        //thirty day path
        return dp[currDay] = min(oneDay, min(sevenDay, thirtyDay));
        //min of all paths
    }
    int mincostTickets(vector<int> &days, vector<int> &costs)
    {
        int lastDay = days[days.size() - 1];
        vector<int> dp(lastDay + 1, -1);
        for (auto i: days)
        {
            isTicketValid.insert(i);
            //Creating valid days hash set
        }
        return Memoization(dp, days, costs, 1);
    }
//==============================================================================================================================
   	//TABULATION
    int mincostTickets(vector<int> &days, vector<int> &costs)
    {
        int lastDay = days[days.size() - 1];
        vector<int> dp(lastDay + 1, 0);
        int index = 0;
        //Index tracking valid days
        for (int day = 1; day <= lastDay; day++)
        {
            if (day < days[index])
            {
                dp[day] = dp[day - 1];
                //If the day is smaller than valid day so no extra cost
            }
            else
            {
                index++;
                //If day exceeds valid days
                //Checking cost of all paths
                int oneDay = costs[0] + dp[day - 1];
                int sevenDay = costs[1] + dp[max(0, day - 7)];
                int thirtyDay = costs[2] + dp[max(0, day - 30)];
                //Min of all paths
                dp[day] = min(oneDay, min(sevenDay, thirtyDay));
            }
        }
        return dp[lastDay];
    }
};
```
