# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
First wrote the basic recurssive code for the problem then just memoized it. When solving this type of problem , the best thing is try to first decide the states of the recurrsion and 90% of the job is done.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
**pass** is the number of days the traveller has purchased the ticket i.e 1,7 or 30 days
        it seems like pass also constitutes a state of the dp. But we purchase ticket(1,7,or 30) 
        every day if we don't have ticket for that day.And then initialise the minimun cost for 
        that day.

      day is the iterator from 0 to days.size()-1.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n) 
where n= days.size()
we are calling the function for each day only once then its result is being stored.

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n) 
Extra space for the memo table.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int travel(vector<int>& days, vector<int>& costs,int pass, int day,vector<int> &memo)
    {
        if(day>=days.size())  // when we have reached end of the array
            return 0;

        if(days[day]<=pass)   // if we have ticket for that day then we don't purchase any and simply increment day
            return travel(days,costs,pass,day+1,memo);

        if(memo[day]!=-1)     // memo table look up
            return memo[day];

        //if we don't have ticket for that day

        int cst=0; // purchasing all types of ticket for a given day and choosing the minimum from them

        cst=costs[0]+travel(days,costs,days[day],day+1,memo);
        cst= min(cst, costs[1]+travel(days,costs,days[day]+6,day+1,memo));
        cst= min(cst,costs[2]+travel(days,costs,days[day]+29,day+1,memo));

        memo[day]=cst;

        return cst;
    }

    int mincostTickets(vector<int>& days, vector<int>& costs) {

        vector<int> memo(days.size(),-1);

        return travel(days,costs,0,0,memo);
    }
};
```

