solutions.content:
**Explaination :**

In this solution ```dp[i]``` means cost, for travelling ```days[i]``` days. In order to minimize cost we check whether it is better to buy 30 days ticket (which will be ```dp[i+1] = dp[k]+costs[2]```), 7 days (which will be ```dp[i+1] = dp[j]+costs[1]```) or 1 day ticket (which will be ```dp[i+1]=min(dp[i]+costs[0]```) using Two Pointers ```k``` and ```j``` to track the day atleast 30 and 7 days before ```i``` respectively. 

**Code :**
```
class Solution {
public:
    int dp[366];
    int mincostTickets(vector<int>& days, vector<int>& costs) {
        int n=days.size(),j=0,k=0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            while(days[i]-days[j]>=7)j++;
            while(days[i]-days[k]>=30)k++;
            dp[i+1]=min(dp[i]+costs[0],min(dp[j]+costs[1],dp[k]+costs[2]));
        }
        return dp[n];
    }
};
```

**Complexity analysis**

* Time Complexity: O(N), where N is the number of calendar days.
* Space Complexity: O(N).

