solutions.content:
Adding 2 solutions with their running times. Complexity of both is linear.

1. Using 2 queues. Running time 22 ms.
```
class Solution {
    public int longestSubarray(int[] nums, int limit) {
        ArrayDeque<Integer> increasing = new ArrayDeque<>();
        ArrayDeque<Integer> decreasing = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int result = 0;
        int startPos = 0;

        for (int i=0 ; i<nums.length ; ++i) {
            while (!increasing.isEmpty() && nums[increasing.getLast()] > nums[i]) {
                increasing.removeLast();
            }
            increasing.addLast(i);
            while (!decreasing.isEmpty() && nums[decreasing.getLast()] < nums[i]) {
                decreasing.removeLast();
            }
            decreasing.addLast(i);

            while (nums[decreasing.getFirst()] - nums[increasing.getFirst()] > limit) {
                if (decreasing.getFirst() < increasing.getFirst()) {
                    startPos = decreasing.removeFirst() + 1;
                } else {
                    startPos = increasing.removeFirst() + 1;
                }
            }
            result = Math.max(result, i-startPos+1);
        }
        return result;
    }
}
```

2. Without queues. Running time 26ms.
```
class Solution {
    public int longestSubarray(int[] nums, int limit) {
        int left = 0;
        int right = 0;
        int min = nums[0];
        int max = nums[0];
        int minPos = 0;
        int maxPos = 0;
        int len = 1; // len can never be zero if we have atleast one element in nums[] because limit >= 0

        while (++right < nums.length) {
            if (nums[right] >= max) {
                max = nums[right];
                maxPos = right;

                if (max - min > limit) {
                    // find new min
                    int i = right - 1;
                    min = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
                    while (i > left && max - nums[i] <= limit) {
                        if (nums[i] < min) {
                            minPos = i;
                            min = nums[i];
                        }
                        i--;
                    }
                    left = i+1;
                    if (min == Integer.MAX_VALUE) {
                        min = nums[left];
                        minPos = left;
                    }
                }
            }
            if (nums[right] <= min) {
                min = nums[right];
                minPos = right;

                if (max - min > limit) {
                    // find new max
                    int i = right - 1;
                    max = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
                    while (i > left && nums[i] - min <= limit) {
                        if (nums[i] > max) {
                            maxPos = i;
                            max = nums[i];
                        }
                        i--;
                    }
                    left = i+1;
                    if (max == Integer.MIN_VALUE) {
                        max = nums[left];
                        maxPos = left;
                    }
                }
            }
            len = Math.max(len, right-left+1);
        }
        return len;
    }
}
