solutions.content:
I am using two heaps + pointer to do this. Keeping the min and max in the heap top, check the diff, if exceeding the limit, then remove the left element until the heap size is <= to the limit.

```
class Solution {
    public int longestSubarray(int[] nums, int limit) {
        PriorityQueue<Integer> pqMin = new PriorityQueue();
        PriorityQueue<Integer> pqMax = new PriorityQueue(Collections.reverseOrder());
        int count = 0;
        int left = -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            pqMin.offer(nums[i]);
            pqMax.offer(nums[i]);
            while (pqMax.peek() - pqMin.peek() > limit) {
                ++left;
                pqMin.remove(nums[left]);
                pqMax.remove(nums[left]);
            }
            count = Math.max(count, pqMin.size());
        }
        return count;
    }
}
