**Aim:** Longest Continuous Subarray With Absolute Diff Less Than or Equal to Limit.
Here diff depends upon Largest and smallest number within the subarray.
We use two pointers start,end to store start and end of subarray.
**Algo:**
1.Maintain largest and smallest number of subarray, check if it is <=limit.
2.If diff greter than limit , we should remove largest and smallest numbers from our subarray.
3.We can use Deque to maintain indices of largest and smallest numbers of subarray.
**Example:**
arr=[8,2,4,7], limit=4
Two Deques,
min-to store indices of potential minimum,Topmost element stores smallest element
max-to store indices of potential maximum numbers.Topmoset element stores largest element.
intially start=end=0n=.arr.length min=empty, max=empty.We run loop till end=n, 
**[1]** start=0,end=0<n
min=0(8) 
max=0(8) . 
max_value-min_value=8-8=0<=limit. so increase window size , end++ and res=1
**[2]** start=0,end=1<n
min=1(2).We removed 8 because, it will never be least in any subarray from start>=0,end=i
max=0,1(8,2)We add 2 beacuse,it may be maximum for subarray from start>=1,end=i
max_value-min_value=8-2=6>limit. It means we need to reduce window size, remove elements from start of min,max deque [as we strored indices in ascending order] with index <=start . start++
**[3]** start=1,end=1<n
min=1(2)
max=1(2).
max_value-min_value=2-2=0<=limit. so increase window size , end++ and res=1
**[4]** start=1,end=2<n
min=1,2(2,4)Add 4 because it may be minimum in subarray where start>=2
max=2(4).Remove 1(2) beacuse 2 will never be maximum for subarray where start>=1.
max_value-min_value=4-2=2<=limit. so increase window size , end++ and res=2
**[5]** start=1,end=3<n
min=1,2,3(2,4,7).
max=3(7)
max_value-min_value=7-2=5>limit. It means we need to reduce window size, remove elements from start of min,max deque [as we strored indices in ascending order]with index <=start . start++
**[6]** start=2,end=3<n
min=2,3(4,7)
max=3(7)
max_value-min_value=7-4=3<=limit. so increase window size , end++ and res=2.
**[7]** start=2,end=4 . end of loop

**Deque** Helps for inserting and deleting from either end.
So we insert from last ,assuming current index may be min/max in future and we remove first when we want reduce window size and remove max/min that are less than or equal to start.
```
class Solution {
    public int longestSubarray(int[] nums, int limit) {
        int n=nums.length,res=0,start=0,end=0;
        Deque<Integer> min=new ArrayDeque<Integer>();
        Deque<Integer> max=new ArrayDeque<Integer>();
        while(end<n){          
            while(!min.isEmpty() && nums[min.peekLast()]>nums[end]) min.removeLast();
            min.addLast(end);
            while(!max.isEmpty() && nums[max.peekLast()]<nums[end]) max.removeLast();
            max.addLast(end);
            int min_val=nums[min.peekFirst()];
            int max_val=nums[max.peekFirst()];
            if(max_val-min_val<=limit){
                res=Math.max(res,end-start+1);
                end++;
            }
            else{
                int skip_index=Math.min(min.peekFirst(), max.peekFirst());
                while(min.peekFirst()<=skip_index) min.removeFirst();
                while(max.peekFirst()<=skip_index) max.removeFirst();
                start=skip_index+1;
            }         
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```

