solutions.content:
July 17, 2020

**Introduction**
It is my first algorithm in my Leetcode mock interview phone screen. The subarray should be continuous based on my analysis. So the array can not be sorted, the order has to be kept. 

One of ideas is to apply slide window technique to find current width if the window meets the requirement of difference between max and min value. 

**TLE concern**
How to keep minimum value and maximum value of sliding window? Do I need to consider maximum heap and minimum heap for values in sliding window? I skipped the consideration and ran into Time Limit Exceeded, so I add some pruning, only call Max and Min in sliding window when current value is Max or Min. 

```
public class Solution {
    public int LongestSubarray(int[] nums, int limit) {

        // subarray should be continuous
        // brute force solution O(n*n)
        // optimal solution using slide window - keep max/ min window count for slide window
        // also keep count of value in slide window as well
        // using hashmap<Int, int>, key - integer value, value - count of number
        // max and min heap to get O(1) for maximum and minimum in sliding window
        // To simplify, use Max/ Min count instead
        if(nums == null || nums.Length == 0 || limit < 0)
            return 0; 

        var length = nums.Length; 

        var map = new Dictionary<int, int>(); 

        var max = 0; 
        var left = 0; 
        var index = 0; 

        // [8, 2, 4, 7], limit = 4
        while(index < length)
        {
            var current = nums[index]; // 7                        

            if(map.Count > 0)
            {
                var maxInWindow = map.Keys.Max();
                var minInWindow = map.Keys.Min(); 

                while(map.Count > 0 && (Math.Abs(maxInWindow - current) > limit || Math.Abs(minInWindow - current) > limit))
                {
                    // slide left pointer
                    var leftValue = nums[left]; // 2
                    map[leftValue]--; // map[8] = 0
                    if(map[leftValue] == 0)
                    {
                        map.Remove(leftValue); //{}
                    }

                    // 
                    if(leftValue == maxInWindow && !map.ContainsKey(leftValue))
                    {
                        if(map.Count == 0)
                        {
                            maxInWindow = current; 
                        }
                        else
                        {
                            maxInWindow = map.Keys.Max();
                        }
                    }

                    if(leftValue == minInWindow && !map.ContainsKey(leftValue))
                    {
                        if(map.Count == 0)
                        {
                           minInWindow = current;
                        }
                        else
                        {
                            minInWindow = map.Keys.Min(); 
                        }
                    }

                    left++; // 1
                }             
            }

            var width = index - left + 1;                 
            max = Math.Max(max, width); // 2

            //add current to map
            if(!map.ContainsKey(current))
            {
                map.Add(current, 0);
            }

            map[current]++; // map[2] = 1  map[4]=1                    

            index++;                
        }

        return max; 
    }
}
```

